column2: No information whatsoever can be inferred from this exceptional value. (e.g, unknown if any surgical procedure of the primary site was performed).
No proper value is applicable in this context (e.g., no surgical resection of the primary site was performed and for cases diagnosed at autopsy).
A proper value is applicable but not known. This event occurred, but the date is unknown (e.g., surgical procedure of the primary site was performed but the date is unknown).
A valid date value is provided in item RX Date Mst Defn Srg [3170], or the date was not expected to have been transmitted.
